A council of the French Church assembled in 744 at Soissons. It seems probable that S. Boniface presided there also. It was occupied with the trial and condemnation of Adalbert and clement, two heretical impostore. Adalbert pretended to possess miraculous powers, such as belong to none but God; and Clement had seduced many persons from the saith by his false doctrine. They were finally con- demned by the council os Rome in 745.
